HEADWORD: Rampage
<hw>Ramp"age</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧mp"⟦asl⟧j; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Ramp</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>Violent or riotous
behavior; a state of excitement, passion, or debauchery; <as>as, to be
on the <ex>rampage</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[Prov. or Low]</mark>
<rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rampage</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rampage
<hw>Ramp"age</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To leap or prance about, as an
animal; to be violent; to rage.</def> <mark>[Prov. or Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rampageous</ent>⟦br⟧
